body:
From a strict typing perspective, going from this signature:

```ts
interface Formatter {
    format(results: LintResult[]): string;
}

class ESLint {
    async loadFormatter(name: string = "stylish"): Promise<Formatter> { /* ... */ }
    // ...
}
```

to this wider return type:

```diff
 interface Formatter {
-    format(results: LintResult[]): string;
+    format(results: LintResult[]): string | Promise<string>;
 }
```

would be a breaking change. But like you all, I'd really like to be able to do this without waiting a year for ESLint v9. I see the argument that it's really the user who's in charge of the return type when they select a formatter. I'd be okay making this change and asking async formatters to document that they may not be compatible with all integrations.
